HEADWORD: Lophobranchii
<hw>Loph`o*bran"chi*i</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>lo`fos</grk> a crest or tuft +
<grk>bra`gchion</grk> gill.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of
teleostean fishes, having the gills arranged in tufts on the branchial
arches, as the Hippocampus and pipefishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

